Description: A Plot-Twist Writing Competition
Rules and Regulations:
No of participants: 01
Word limit: 600-1000 words
Time: 1 hour

Rules and Regulations-
Participants will have to write a story based on any of the following options:
-Plot mixer
-You have to combine two movie plots out of the given movies and make a new story.
-You can mix more than two plots, for which you will get bonus points.
-You cannot combine more than four plots. 
-You can add or remove characters from the original plot, or create new characters as you wish.
-You can make slight changes to the storyline, but the plot should largely be a mix/mashup of two movie plots you have chosen. All elements of two plots do not need to be included.

Script Starter
-You have to start writing a new story by choosing one of the opening lines provided in the lines list.
-Your story must have a clear link to the opening line, if not negative points will be awarded.
-You are not allowed to start with any lines that are not among the given lines list.

Scenarios
-You have to write a new story based on one or more situations chosen by you from the situations list.
-You can mix more than two plots, for which you will get bonus points. 
-You cannot combine more than four plots.
-You can make slight changes to the chosen situations, but the story must have a clear link to the chosen situation, if not negative points will be awarded.
